But A, E are prime; primes are also least [Vll. 21], and ’ the least measure those which have the same ratio the same number of times, the antecedent the antecedent and the consequent the consequent [VII. 20] ; therefore E measures A, as antecedent antecedent. Q. E. D.

The comment ol Clavius is:

“Est autem res admirabilis huius propositionis demon- stratio Nam ex eo quod b dicatur non metiri ipsum a, ostendit, demonstratione affirmativa, b ipsum a metiti, quod - videtur fieri non posse. Nam si quis demonstrare instituat Socratem esse album, ex eo quod non est albus, paradoxum aliquid et inopinatum in medio videatur afferre: cui tamen non absimile quid factum hic est in numeris ab Euclide, et in aliis nonnullis propositionibus quae sequuntur.”

Now the edition of Clavius was the Euclid recommended by T. Ceva to Saccheri. .

This recondite legerdemain ol logie, so striking to Cardan and Clavius, seized with a more permanent fascination the adroit mind ol the subtle Saccheri. Itis the dominant note of the Lopica demonstrativo, and thence adventures the quest of the holy grail, Euclid's Parallel Postulate.
